name: Rache Bartmoss
description: Rache Bartmossis a legendarynetrunnerin theCyberpunk-series who in the early21st centurybecame notorious as the man who caused theDataKrashand killed the oldNet. He invented theDemonandBloodhoundseries of programs. He also co-authored theRache Bartmoss' Guide to the NetandBrainware Blowoutbooks alongsideSpider Murphy. At just four years old, Rache Bartmoss started netrunning for the first time. Because of his inexperience with the Net, he used his real identity, oblivious to the potential risks.
